First, no need to specify frames when using constraints. Let the auto-layout engine do the work for you.

Second, constraints can all be set in `viewDidLoad()` -- you don&#39;t need anything in `viewWillLayoutSubviews()`.

Third, it&#39;s not quite clear where you want the picker view to show, or why you are putting it in a stack view? I&#39;m assuming you want the picker to start at 50-pts below the bottom of the nav bar, and that you&#39;ll be adding additional elements to the stack view?

So, a couple tips:

- During development, give views contrasting background colors to make it easy to see frames at run-time
- Use `Debug View Hierarchy` to help figure out bad / missing constraints
- Group your code by logical association. Such as
 - instantiate objects
 - set object properties
 - add subviews
 - set constraints

