Initially, I plan to use Apache `isBase64`, to validate the input before passing into `Base64.decode`.

https://github.com/apache/commons-codec/blob/master/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/codec/binary/Base64.java

Later, I notice the logic is not strict enough. They do not check for the following rules mentioned in https://stackoverflow.com/a/8571544/72437

 - Check that the length is a multiple of 4 characters
 - Check that every character is in the set A-Z, a-z, 0-9, +, / except for padding at the end which is 0, 1 or 2 &#39;=&#39; characters

Hence, I modify Apache `isBase64` with the above rules. Note, for simplicity, I do not accept white space as valid base64 in my usage purpose.

